{"sequence":103,"timestamp":"2026-04-21T08:05:38.011948189Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-8003804f","body":"finding_summary: `project create-from-bead` still permits a parallel project when the only existing active lineage row is a legacy `run_id: null` attempt. The new read-only helper explicitly drops every non-terminal row without a run ID (`src/adapters/fs.rs:5089-5104`), `execute_create_from_bead` relies on that helper for its duplicate guard (`src/cli/project.rs:587-597`), and the integration test now locks that behavior in as success (`tests/cli.rs:13549-13594`). In an upgraded workspace with one of these legacy active rows, create-time validation will silently ignore the existing same-bead attempt, mint a second project, and leave the ambiguity to be \"repaired\" only later on a start-time write. That misses the bead's stated goal of surfacing or blocking inconsistent active lineage at create time instead of allowing another task to be created.\nremediation_hint: Treat non-terminal runless rows as an inconsistent/orphaned active lineage that blocks creation with a repair hint, or run the same legacy-row repair before duplicate detection so create-time behavior matches start-time behavior.","dedup_key":"f0bc93980c4c5d37ab3114dacd49bd83468cb16595f23f0d6108cf2fbf8c2019","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260421035000","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
